"eighty years ago, liberals watched in horror as their ideology of freedom did little to stop the atrocities committed by Adolf Hitler. For a time, the Greatest Generation created social democratic regimes designed to ensure that this never happened again, while giving all people a stake in their society. However, a combination of racist backlash and elite chafing against the obligations of this new order had produced a political retrenchment that had allowed for corporations to accumulate vast amounts of power, by which the nostrum of "wealth creation" was used to justify this state of affairs. But in the end, what was not saved or strengthened was liberal capitalist democracy, but a corporatized cartel economy that undercut the very free market principles they claimed"
